SIMPLE: undertaking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undertaking
<hw>Un`der*tak"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one
who undertakes, or engages in, any project or business.</def>
<rj><au>Hakluyt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is undertaken; any business, work, or
project which a person engages in, or attempts to perform; an
enterprise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Specifically, the business of an undertaker, or the
management of funerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A promise or pledge; a guarantee.</def> <rj><au>A.
Trollope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undertapster</ent>⟦br⟧
